      "content": "The exhaustion of maintaining a performance when you feel hollow inside is an immense burden to carry alone. This sense of feeling like an actor in a dead play highlights a deep despair about the authenticity of your daily life. Therapy can offer a place to gently dismantle the script you feel forced to follow and help you explore what it means to define yourself outside of those old roles. Please consider leaning on a professional who can help lift some of this weight.",
